Danlann is easy to use and powerful command line web photo gallery
generator. Refer to Danlann manual for detailed usage information, examples
and customization possibilites.

Current Danlann implementation generates XHTML files, which conform to W3C
standards as much as possible. If you find a bug... please report it. It is
really appreciated.

On other side, Danlann developers do not have enough time to deal with
quirks of different web browsers. If you your preferred web browser have
problems with displaying generated pages, then report bug to team
developing this web browser, please.

Requirements:
- Python 2.4 or later

    http://www.python.org/

- ImageMagick or GraphicsMagick

    http://www.imagemagick.org/script/index.php
    http://www.graphicsmagick.org/

- spark python module
    
    http://pages.cpsc.ucalgary.ca/~aycock/spark/

- libxml 2.6.x Python bindings

    http://xmlsoft.org/python.html

- exiv2 software

    http://www.exiv2.org/


See INSTALL file for installation details (standard ac/am stuff).

Installation and usage instructions for impatient

    1. Install

        ./configure --prefix=$HOME/opt
        make install

    2. Create gallery configuration file and album files (see examples
       directory or Danlann manual).

    3. Run Danlann

        export PYTHONPATH=$HOME/opt/share/python2.4/site-packages
        export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/opt/bin

        danlann gallery.ini
